The President hosted a film screening of "To Kill a Mockingbird" at the White House to commemorate its 50th anniversary. Guests included local students, the actress who played Scout, and the widow of Gregory Peck who played Atticus Finch. The President thanked the American Film Institute, NBC Universal, and USA Network for their efforts. He also expressed gratitude to the actress for bringing the character of Scout to life and to the Peck family for their support. The President described the novel as a timeless American classic and one of his favorite books.